## Public And Authentication Screens

### Landing/Home

- Route: `/:locale`
- Roles: Public.
- Purpose: Public Zoovana CMS/landing entry with sections for hero, services, adopt pet, shelter, join, offer, products, pricing, about, marquee.
- Entry points: Root URL, logo links, dashboard back buttons.
- Layout: Header, landing sections, footer, scroll/navigation dots in the landing component set.
- Components/actions: Join/register calls to auth screens; adopt/donate/lost-found/provider/marketplace links.
- Data: Mostly static localized messages and public display assets.
- States: Normal responsive landing, image fallback components.
- Mobile notes: Keep as a public marketing/home shell; mobile app may replace with an authenticated role picker and only expose public web flows through webviews/deep links.

### Auth Screens

- Routes: `/:locale/login`, `/:locale/signup`, `/:locale/register`, `/:locale/register/shopOwner`, `/:locale/verify-email`, `/:locale/forgot-password`, `/:locale/reset-password`, `/:locale/pending-approval`.
- Roles: Public, unverified, or authenticated pending user depending on screen.
- Purpose: Account access, registration, password recovery, email OTP verification, pending role/approval status.
- Entry points: Header links, protected-route redirects, login errors, password reset emails.
- Layout: Auth layout, language switcher, card-like forms.
- Inputs:
  - Login: email, password, social login; may trigger role selection for social login when backend returns `requires_role_selection`.
  - Register/signup: email, full name, password, phone number, selected role IDs; validation via Zod in `lib/validations/auth/*`.
  - Verify email: OTP input, email query parameter, resend action.
  - Forgot/reset: email, OTP/new password/reset token flow.
  - Pending approval: status details and role display from session.
- Actions: submit credentials, register, verify OTP, resend OTP, request password reset, reset password, refresh session token.
- Data/API: `api/services/auth.js` calling `/api/v1/auth/register`, `/verify-email`, `/resend-verification`, `/forgot-password`, `/verify-otp`, `/reset-password`, `/change-password`, `/me/roles`; public roles from `/api/v1/roles`.
- States: Loading buttons, server errors, role-selection modal/state, pending approval, verified redirect.
- Mobile notes: OTP should use native one-time-code input; social role picker should be a bottom sheet; preserve RTL support.

### Profile

- Route: `/:locale/profile`
- Roles: Authenticated.
- Purpose: User profile/business info hub; also used by livestock quick actions through query tabs such as `?tab=animals`, `?tab=health`, `?tab=schedule`, `?tab=business`.
- Entry points: Top bar/user menu, livestock dashboard quick actions, shelter/shop settings links.
- Layout: Profile client component with likely sidebar/tabs.
- Data/API: current user profile from `users.js` `/api/v1/users/me/profile`; business info from `business.js`.
- Actions: update profile/business data, possibly change password through auth components.
- Mobile notes: Convert tabbed/side profile layout to stacked tabs or segmented control.

### Adopt

- Route: `/:locale/adopt`
- Roles: Public/authenticated.
- Purpose: Browse animals available for adoption and submit adoption interest/application.
- Entry points: Landing sections, shelter flow, public nav.
- Layout: `AdoptPageClient`, animal cards, skeletons, detail/application interactions.
- Data/API: shelter service animal/adoption APIs; public shelter base URL.
- Components/actions: animal list cards, filters/search as implemented in client, adoption application creation, contract route after approval.
- States: `AnimalSkeleton`, empty/no animals, loading/error.
- Mobile notes: Use card list and filter sheet; avoid desktop grid density.

### Adoption Contract

