## Navigation Map

**Public**

- Home -> Login/Register/Adopt/Donate/Lost & Found/Provider/Marketplace.
- Adopt -> Adoption application -> Adoption contract.
- Lost & Found -> Submit lost/found report.

**Authenticated dashboard entry**

- `/dashboard` resolves by role.
- Multi-role users can use the side role switcher to jump to Shop, Shelter, Livestock, Volunteer, Pet Owner, or Provider dashboards.

**Shop flow**

- Shop Overview -> View All recent orders -> Marketplace Orders.
- Branches create/update/delete feed branch selector.
- Products -> Variants, imports, publish to marketplace -> Admin marketplace approvals.
- Inventory and purchase orders depend on selected branch and variants.
- Settings -> Marketplace Activation wizard -> generate API key -> activate marketplace.

**Shelter flow**

- Shelter Overview -> all shelter operations.
- Animals -> Medical/Vaccinations/Adoptions/Kennel/Animal Care workflows by animal.
- Lost & Found -> matches -> reunite or transfer found report to intake/animals.
- Volunteers -> approve volunteer -> create shift -> volunteer signs in/out.
- Adoptions -> detail -> status decision -> schedule event -> outcome -> contract.

**Pet owner/provider flow**

- Pet Owner Services -> Booking Request -> Provider Bookings.
- Provider accepts/declines/completes -> Pet Owner Bookings payment/review.
- Pet Owner/Provider Messages share chat threads.

**Admin flow**

- Admin Dashboard -> Quick Access.
- Marketplace Approvals -> Product/Category queues -> detail -> approve/reject.
- Provider Verification -> Pending/Approved/Rejected/Audit -> profile review -> approve/reject.
- Animal Lookups -> Domains -> Categories -> Pet Types -> Breeds taxonomy.
- Data Management -> Tenants/Products/Categories/Branches.

## Global Mobile Adaptation Notes

- Large `DataTable` screens should become searchable card lists with sort/filter bottom sheets and explicit selection mode.
- Desktop hover-only actions must become visible overflow menus or swipe/action buttons.
- Modals with complex forms should become full-screen native screens or sheets with save/cancel in the header/footer.
- Charts should include accessible summaries; some placeholder charts may be lower priority than operational lists.
- Locale/RTL must be first-class; Arabic text and right-to-left navigation are already supported on web.
- File/image upload flows appear in products, animals, providers, imports, and lost/found; native rebuild should use camera/gallery/document pickers.
- Location fields should use native maps where possible.
- Time/date fields for shifts, bookings, events, vaccinations, and care logs should use native pickers.
- Notifications/toasts are web-style; mobile should map important events to banners, snackbars, and push notifications where backend supports it.